    "Agent profiles typically encompass basic information such as age, gender, and career [20], as well as psychology information, reflecting the personalities of the agent, and social information, detailing the relationships between agents [21].",
    "The choice of information to profile the agent is largely determined by the specific application scenarios.",
    "For instance, if the application aims to study human cognitive process, then the psychology information becomes pivotal.",
    "After identifying the types of profile information, the next important problem is to create specific profiles for the agents.",
    "Existing literature commonly employs the following three strategies.Handcrafting method: in this method, agent profiles are manually specified."
